<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="155" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,848,1184]" pageId="6" pageNumber="155">
Diagnosis. Medusa with 
<number box="[457,470,848,872]" pageId="6" pageNumber="155" value="4.0">4</number>
primary radial canals, branching repeatedly at various levels; no centripetal canals; with or without secondary tentacles and warts; gonads with 
<number box="[692,705,883,907]" pageId="6" pageNumber="155" value="8.0">8</number>
rows of transversely folded; no ocelli. Polyp unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,848,1184]" pageId="6" pageNumber="155">
Remarks. The genus is a currently monotypic genus. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bigelow, H. B." box="[783,955,917,941]" journalOrPublisher="siphonophores and ctenophores of the &quot; Albatross &quot; Philippine Expedition. Bulletin of the United States National Museum, (100) 1" pageId="6" pageNumber="155" pagination="279 - 362" part="5" refString="Bigelow, H. B. 1919. Hydromeudsae, siphonophores and ctenophores of the &quot; Albatross &quot; Philippine Expedition. Bulletin of the United States National Museum, (100) 1 (5): 279 - 362, pls. 39 - 43." title="Hydromeudsae" type="journal article" year="1919">
Bigelow (
<number box="[891,947,917,941]" pageId="6" pageNumber="155" value="1919.0">1919</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
assumed that the side branches of the radial canals were actually centripetal canals. He therefore synonymized that the genus with 
<taxonomicName box="[1072,1189,952,976]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Bythotiaridae" genus="Calycopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anthoathecata" pageId="6" pageNumber="155" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1072,1189,952,976]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="155">Calycopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kramp, P. L." box="[1203,1356,952,976]" journalOrPublisher="Dana-Report" pageId="6" pageNumber="155" pagination="1 - 283" part="46" refString="Kramp, P. L. 1959. The Hydromedusae of the Atlantic Ocean and adjacent waters. Dana-Report, 46: 1 - 283." title="The Hydromedusae of the Atlantic Ocean and adjacent waters" type="journal article" year="1959">
Kramp (
<number box="[1293,1349,952,976]" pageId="6" pageNumber="155" value="1959.0">1959</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
outlined the taxonomic history of the genus and contested Bigelow’s view of the growth direction of the radial canals. Kramp thinks that the branching radial canals arise indeed through branching during ontogeny and he thus has an argument to maintain the genus. The diminution of the canal width towards the periphery is a good evidence to support this view. 
<bibRefCitation author="Schuchert, P." box="[136,323,1091,1115]" journalOrPublisher="Revue Suisse de Zoologie" pageId="6" pageNumber="155" pagination="441 - 507" part="116" refString="Schuchert, P. 2009. The European athecate hydroids and their medusae (Hydrozoa, Cnidaria): Filifera Part 5. Revue Suisse de Zoologie, 116 (3 - 4): 441 - 507." title="The European athecate hydroids and their medusae (Hydrozoa, Cnidaria): Filifera Part 5" type="journal article" year="2009">
Schuchert (
<number box="[260,316,1091,1115]" pageId="6" pageNumber="155" value="2009.0">2009</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
assumed that neither known the polyp stage of 
<taxonomicName box="[860,977,1091,1115]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Bythotiaridae" genus="Calycopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anthoathecata" pageId="6" pageNumber="155" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[860,977,1091,1115]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="155">Calycopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
nor of 
<taxonomicName box="[1064,1153,1091,1115]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Bythotiaridae" genus="Sibogita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anthoathecata" pageId="6" pageNumber="155" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1064,1153,1091,1115]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="155">Sibogita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, further discussions on the validity of 
<taxonomicName box="[253,342,1125,1149]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Bythotiaridae" genus="Sibogita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anthoathecata" pageId="6" pageNumber="155" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[253,342,1125,1149]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="155">Sibogita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are premature.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,848,1184]" box="[189,846,1160,1184]" pageId="6" pageNumber="155">This genus is recorded from Chinese waters for the first time.</paragraph>
